uns along the bottom.\n\nA rear view of the man’s clean brown hair appears against a bright lake and tree-lined shore. Large green and white text overlays the scene: “up to 5x stronger.” A hand reaches in and runs through the back of his hair, lifting and ruffling it to show texture and movement. The man tilts his head slightly as his hair catches the light. The scene cuts to a lively indoor lounge or porch area with several young adults piled playfully on a patterned couch. The blonde woman lies across or leans over the dark-haired man, laughing, while other friends gather around them. Small text at the bottom notes “compared to an ordinary shampoo,” though some fine print is hard to read.\n\nBack outdoors near the pool table and trees, the man lies back while a woman’s hand strokes his face and hair. The word “shinier” appears in large white letters with a green underline. The blonde woman leans down over him and kisses him, her hand cradling the back of his head. Their faces fill the image as they kiss, emphasizing his clean, touchable hair.\n\nAnother outdoor view shows the man from behind, wearing a black shirt, with a pool cue resting horizontally across his shoulders behind his neck. His brown hair looks clean and slightly wavy. Large white and green text reads “no flakes guaranteed,” with fine print along the bottom. The view moves closer to the back of his head, showing the hair near his neck with no visible white flakes. The blonde woman then kisses the side or back of his neck while holding his head in both hands; her pale hair falls forward as she presses close to him.\n\nNear the end, the man stands alone outdoors in daylight, facing forward with a calm, confident expression. Behind him are shiny silver trailer-like structures, an orange canopy, and a blue sky, suggesting an outdoor event or campsite. He looks straight ahead with clean, tousled hair.\n\nThe final product display returns to the white background with floating citrus slices. Two bright green Garnier Fructis bottles stand side by side, the left bottle labeled as the fortifying anti-dandruff shampoo and the right appearing to be a matching companion hair-care product. The bottles are glossy, with white brand lettering and small circular cap details near the bottom. The image moves in close on the shampoo bottle, showing “Garnier Fructis” prominently while orange and lime slices drift behind it. The commercial ends on a pale citrus-colored background with a single green lime slice floating on the left.",
